│ 1952   //                                                                                  │
│ 1953   //    tmp = *P;  for () { if (c) tmp +=1; } *P = tmp;                               │
│ 1954   //                                                                                  │
│ 1955   // is not safe, because *P may only be valid to access if 'c' is true.              │
│ 1956   //                                                                                  │
│ 1957   // The safety property divides into two parts:                                      │
│ 1958   // p1) The memory may not be dereferenceable on entry to the loop.  In this         │
│ 1959   //    case, we can't insert the required load in the preheader.                     │
│ 1960   // p2) The memory model does not allow us to insert a store along any dynamic       │
│ 1961   //    path which did not originally have one.                                       │
│ 1962   //                                                                                  │
